measures.name: zedgvrf_with_doas
measures.description: Adds VRF system with multiple indoor units connected to an outdoor unit.
measures.modeler_description: Multiple units allows for capacity variation and simultaneous heating and cooling. Each zone in the model was served by a VRF indoor terminal unit and the DOAS. Performance curves for the outdoor terminal unit entered into the model with a resistive defrost and heat recovery. Kitchen, gym and the cafeteria were served by their own outdoor units.

measures.name: aedg_office_hvac_vav_ch_w
measures.description: Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a high efficiency multizone variable air volume (VAV) HVAC system (one system per floor).  The multizone VAV system (centralized cooling with zone level heating) is applied to all space types.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% Small and Medium Office AEDG.
measures.modeler_description: Airloops are dedicated to the multizone VAV cooling system and have variable speed fan operation, hot water coil heating, and chilled water coil cooling.  The cold deck has outdoor air reset on the supply air temperature.  Heating is provided at the zone level with hot water baseboard heaters.  The chiller for the VAV is air-cooled.

measures.description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. measures.modeler_description: For the most part consumption data comes from the tabular EnergyPlus results, however there are a few requests added for time series results. The structure of the report uses bootstrap, and the graphs use dimple js.

steps.description: Adds VRF system with multiple indoor units connected to an outdoor unit.
steps.name: zedgvrf_with_doas

steps.description: Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a high efficiency multizone variable air volume (VAV) HVAC system (one system per floor).  The multizone VAV system (centralized cooling with zone level heating) is applied to all space types.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules. da_descriptions.name: Option 1 Name
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Adds VRF system with multiple indoor units connected to an outdoor unit.

da_descriptions.name: aedg_office_hvac_vav_ch_w
da_descriptions.description: Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a high efficiency multizone variable air volume (VAV) HVAC system (one system per floor).  The multizone VAV system (centralized cooling with zone level heating) is applied to all space types.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% Small and Medium Office AEDG.

da_descriptions.name: Load breakdown
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Report provides annual and monthly views into heat gains and losses for envelope and internal loads.

da_descriptions.name: Option 1 Name
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

steps.description: Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a high efficiency multizone variable air volume (VAV) HVAC system (one system per floor).  The multizone VAV system (centralized cooling with zone level heating) is applied to all space types.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% Small and Medium Office AEDG.

steps.description: Adds VRF system with multiple indoor units connected to an outdoor unit.
steps.name: zedgvrf_with_doas

steps.description: Option 1 Description: Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a high efficiency multizone variable air volume (VAV) HVAC system (one system per floor).  The multizone VAV system (centralized cooling with zone level heating) is applied to all space types.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% Small and Medium Office AEDG.
steps.name: Option 1 Name
